+	// Run commit I/O under the caller's ClientContext, not a freshly-opened
+	// Connection. A new Connection gets its own DuckDB transaction with a
+	// new transaction_id/start_time whose CatalogSet visibility rules
+	// (see duckdb/src/catalog/catalog_set.cpp, UseTimestamp) cannot see
+	// CatalogSet entries — notably registered s3 secrets — that were
+	// created by the caller's still-active transaction. That makes
+	// SecretManager::LookupSecret return no match during commit-time S3
+	// URL resolution, and DuckDB's httpfs resolver then falls through to
+	// AWS virtual-hosted defaults, HTTP 403 against any non-AWS endpoint.
 	try {
